## Dataset

**Source:** Food.com recipe dataset (`dataset.csv`, gzip-compressed)
**Size:** 375,703 recipes × 16 columns
**Missing values:** none

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `RecipeId` | int | Unique recipe identifier |
| `Name` | string | Recipe title |
| `CookTime` | int | Cook time, in seconds |
| `PrepTime` | int | Prep time, in seconds |
| `TotalTime` | int | Cook + prep time, in seconds |
| `RecipeIngredientParts` | string | Ingredients as a packed R-style vector: `c("blueberries", "granulated sugar", ...)` |
| `Calories` | float | Calories per serving |
| `FatContent` | float | Total fat (g) |
| `SaturatedFatContent` | float | Saturated fat (g) |
| `CholesterolContent` | float | Cholesterol (mg) |
| `SodiumContent` | float | Sodium (mg) |
| `CarbohydrateContent` | float | Carbohydrates (g) |
| `FiberContent` | float | Dietary fiber (g) |
| `SugarContent` | float | Sugar (g) |
| `ProteinContent` | float | Protein (g) |
| `RecipeInstructions` | string | Instructions, packed the same way as ingredients |

**Nutrition summary** (the 9 features the recommender matches on):

| Statistic | Calories | Fat (g) | Sugar (g) | Protein (g) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Mean | 270.2 | 12.1 | 8.7 | 12.4 |
| Median | 238.7 | 9.8 | 5.3 | 6.8 |
| Max | 1,993.8 | 98.9 | 39.9 | 181.9 |

**Data quality note:** `CookTime`/`PrepTime`/`TotalTime` contain a few extreme outliers (max `CookTime` ≈ 504 days), likely parsing artifacts from the original ISO 8601 duration strings (e.g. `PT24H45M`). Worth clipping before using time as a filter — it doesn't affect nutrition-based matching, since that only uses the 9 nutrition columns.
